    <p>The Lovelace textbook introduces probability from scratch with interactive visualizations. This page assumes basic familiarity with probability and focuses on the Bayesian update machinery that subsequent chapters build on. The textbook also covers joint distributions, marginalization, and independence, which are prerequisites for the graphical models in Chapter 3.</p>

